HEADWORD: Misrecollect
<hw>Mis*rec`ol*lect"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <def>To
have an erroneous remembrance of; to suppose erroneously that one
recollects.</def> <rj><au>Hitchcock.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

